title: Cloak AC-6 — occurrence counters and message state survive save/restore
story: cloak-of-darkness
description: ADR-210 AC-6 (added Phase 6, additive to the frozen golden six).
  Stumble once (first-time ordinal tramples the message), save, stumble to
  obliteration, then restore — the restored world must carry occurrence
  count 1 and state trampled with no author-written persistence code, so
  the two post-restore dark entries are the 2nd and 3rd, obliterating the
  message again.

---

# Dark entry 1: first-time ordinal fires, message trampled
> south
[OK: contains "Blundering around in the dark isn't a good idea!"]

> north
[OK: contains "Foyer of the Opera House"]

$save ac6-one-stumble

# Dark entries 2 and 3: third-time ordinal obliterates
> south
[OK: contains "Blundering around in the dark isn't a good idea!"]

> north
[OK: contains "Foyer of the Opera House"]

> south
[OK: contains "Blundering around in the dark isn't a good idea!"]

> north
[OK: contains "Foyer of the Opera House"]

# Back to one stumble: chord.occurrence.* and chord.state.* are world
# state, so the save carries them (AC-6's "no author persistence code")
$restore ac6-one-stumble

# If the counter restored to 1, these are entries 2 and 3 — obliteration
> south
[OK: contains "Blundering around in the dark isn't a good idea!"]

> north
[OK: contains "Foyer of the Opera House"]

> south
[OK: contains "Blundering around in the dark isn't a good idea!"]

> north
[OK: contains "Foyer of the Opera House"]

# Shed the cloak and read: obliterated is the lose ending
> west
[OK: contains "Cloakroom"]

> remove cloak
[OK: contains "You take off the velvet cloak"]

> hang cloak on hook
[OK: contains "put the velvet cloak on the brass hook"]

> east
[OK: contains "Foyer of the Opera House"]

> south
[OK: contains "Foyer Bar"]

> read message
[OK: contains "trampled beyond recognition"]
[OK: contains "You have lost"]
[EVENT: true, type="story.defeat"]
